- "Top-performing" refers to the highest total sales;
- "Recent activity" is represented by the recency score and rank;
- The query ranks sellers and products by total sales for each customer.

- "blossoms" refers to products;
- "garnered the most attention" refers to high sales amounts;
- "admiration" refers to high average ratings and a significant number of reviews;
- "gardeners" refers to sellers.

- "stars" refers to customers;
- "shone" refers to placing an order;
- "newsletter" refers to the newsletter subscription status in the database.

- "category 1" refers to a specific category of products;
- "at least 10 admirers" means the product has more than 10 reviews;
- "highest average admiration scores" refers to the highest average review scores;
- "top 5 stars" means the top 5 products based on the average review score.

- 'popular seller' refers to the seller with seller_id = 1;
- 'purchased more than once' means the product has been ordered more than once;
- 'listed from the highest to the lowest score' means the results are ordered by the average review score in descending order.

- 'Stars of the show' refers to the top 10 best-selling products;
- 'Sales performance' is determined by the total sales amount;
- 'Recent admirers' are customers who have recently purchased these products;
- 'Recency scores' measure how recently a customer has interacted with a product;
- 'Recency ranks' indicate the position of a customer's recency score among all customers.
